CommonFields.Title: Rheological and mechanical properties of PVC/CaCO3 nanocomposites prepared by in situ polymerization
CommonFields.Author: Xie, Xiao-Lin
Liu, Qing-Xi
Li, Robert Kwok-Yiu
Zhou, Xing-Ping
Zhang, Qing-Xin
Yu, Zhong-Zhen

CommonFields.Location: Department of Chemistry, Huazhong University of Science and Technology, Wuhan 430074, China

MatrixComponent.ManufacturerOrSourceName: Wuhan Gedian Chemical Group Co. Ltd

Mixing.Description: The PVC/nanoCaCO3 compounded resins were synthesized by batch suspension polymerization of vinyl chloride (VC) in the presence of CaCO3 nanoparticles. Poly(vinyl acetate) (PVA) and hydroxyl propyl cellulose (HPMC) were used as suspension agents. The initiator used was a mixture of azobisisobutyronitrile (AIBN) and 2-ethylhexyl peroxydicarbonate (EHP). After the conversion of VC reached 85%, the polymerization was stopped
Mixing.Mixer: Stainless steel jacket reaction vessel of 30-L capacity fitted with four equally spaced stainless steel baffles

Mixing.Description: The mixtures (100 parts PVC/nanoCaCO3 compounded resins, 7 parts XP-301, 2 parts ACR-401, 0.6 part paraffin wax (intermediate lubricant), and 0.8 part stearic acid) were mixed in a high-speed mixer
Above mixtures were plasticized by a two-roll mill

MoldingInfo.Description: Composite plates with dimensions 200 x 80 x 3.2 mm were compression-molded at 175°C for 8 min, with a 5 min preheating period

Scanning_Electron_Microscopy.Description: SEM was used to observe the morphologies of the fracture surfaces of all composites. The specimens were coated with a thin layer of gold prior to SEM examination

Dynamic_Mechanical_Analysis.Description: DMA was conducted at a fixed frequency of 10 Hz and oscillation amplitude of 0.15 mm. The temperature range studied was from -20 to 130°C with a heating rate of 1°C/min.

Thermogravimetric_Analysis.Description: The weight loss against temperature was measured at a heating rate of 5°C/min in a helium environment from 50 to 400°C

Rheometery.Description: The capillary die used had a length (L) to diameter (D) ratio of 40/1 and an entrance angle of 180°

DynamicProperties.Description: Variation of storage modulus with temperature
Variation of tan d with temperature
